org.morphml.networkml.schema
Class Networkml

java.lang.Object
  org.morphml.networkml.schema.Networkml

public class Networkml
extends java.lang.Object

The main elements which make up a NetworkML compliant document.

Java class for NetworkML complex type.

The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

 <complexType name="NetworkML">
   <complexContent>
     <restriction base="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyType">
       <sequence>
         <group ref="{http://morphml.org/metadata/schema}metadata"/>
         <group ref="{http://morphml.org/networkml/schema}CoreNetworkElements"/>
       </sequence>
       <attribute name="name" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
       <attribute name="lengthUnits" type="{http://morphml.org/metadata/schema}LengthUnits" />
       <attribute name="length_units" type="{http://morphml.org/metadata/schema}LengthUnits" />
       <attribute name="volumeUnits" type="{http://morphml.org/metadata/schema}VolumeUnits" default="cubic_millimeter" />
     </restriction>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

getGroups

public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getGroups()
Gets the value of the groups property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the groups property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getGroups().add(newItem);

Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list String
